    + added new locking schemes:
      HB_SET_DBFLOCK_CL53EXT = 4
        Clipper's ntxlock2.obj - I'm not sure it's exactly the same
        Clipper documentation gives differ information here - I will
        have to make my own tests checking what Clipper really locks
        so be careful with using it simultaneously with Clipper
        application in network environment. Anyhow for xHarbour
        applications could be safely used. It emulates shared locks
        so it's very efficient in systems which doesn't have it and
        moves maximum file size to 4'000'000'000 - probably the best
        locking mode for FAT32. It could be used for DBFNTX and DBFCDX.
      HB_SET_DBFLOCK_XHB64 = 5
        xHarbour locking scheme for long files - over 4GB. It needs
        long file support in OS. Effectively it does not reduce file size.
        Please test it in Windows - I made test in Linux and it works
        correctly.

